Mouth moderate in size, nearly as long as wide. Lips large, covered with papillae; size of papillae decreasing towards posterior margin of lower lip; central buccal papilla absent. Upper lip folded over itself. Maxillary barbel short; base of barbel united to lips, with free tip. Lower lip not reaching anterior margin of coracoid. Medial end of premaxillary teeth series curved inwards. Premaxillae (
Fig. 3
) and dentary narrow and elongate. Dentary strongly curved inwards. Teeth slightly thick, well developed, with long crown and large lateral cusp; its distal edge slightly curved inward. Three to four pairs of well developed predorsal plates. Cheek plates not eversible; without associated hypertrophied odontodes (
Fig. 4
).
